Findings: AP radiograph of the chest was reviewed in comparison to. The right internal jugular line tip is at the level of low SVC. Heart size and mediastinum are stable. Bibasal areas of atelectasis have progressed in the interim. There is interval improvement of the left perihilar opacity. No pneumothorax or interval increase in pleural effusion demonstrated. Pleural plaques along the left chest wall are redemonstrated as well as the rib fractures.
